  "text": "Watch events flow through multiple layers in the Kubernetes ecosystem from etcd to client applications:\n\n1. **MVCC Store Event Generation (etcd)**:\n   - In `github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd` at `server/mvcc/watcher.go`, the `watchStream` struct (line 99) implements the `WatchStream` interface (line 37). This struct watches the MVCC key-value store for changes and generates watch events when keys are modified, deleted, or created. The watchStream reads from the MVCC store and produces events that are sent through a channel.\n\n2. **Etcd gRPC API Layer**:\n   - In `github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd` at `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/watch.go`, the `serverWatchStream` struct (line 121) receives watch events from the mvcc.WatchStream. It implements the gRPC server interface for watch operations and sends events to connected clients. The `sendLoop()` method (line 381) reads events from the mvcc.WatchStream's channel and sends them over the gRPC stream to clients.\n\n3. **Kubernetes API Server Cache Layer**:\n   - In `github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes-kubernetes` at `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/cacher.go`, the `Cacher` struct (line 250) is the main caching layer that wraps storage backends. It coordinates between the underlying etcd storage and watch distribution.\n   - In `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/watch_cache.go`, the `watchCache` struct (line 91) maintains an in-memory cache of objects and manages watch event distribution. It receives events from the storage layer and broadcasts them to multiple watchers.\n   - In `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/cache_watcher.go`, the `cacheWatcher` struct (line 53) represents individual watchers receiving events from the watchCache. Each cacheWatcher delivers filtered events to a specific client's watch stream.\n\n4. **Client-Side Watch Handler**:\n   - In `github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes-client-go` at `tools/cache/reflector.go`, the `Reflector` struct (line 59) receives watch events from the Kubernetes API server's watch stream. The `ListAndWatch` method (line 348) implements the main loop that maintains a watch connection to the API server and processes incoming events, updating a local cache store to keep it synchronized with server state.\n\nThe complete flow is: etcd MVCC store → serverWatchStream → Kubernetes Cacher (with watchCache and cacheWatcher distributing events) → Reflector (client-side watch handler) → local informer cache."
